A unique "electronic goods ticket" for return goods Setouchi City added with hometown tax: Sanyo Newspaper Digital | San Diego
"E Street Gift."
to make contact with a dedicated device
Setonai City announced on July 27 that it would add its own e-machi gift to the home tax return.
It is available at a member store in the city from November.
It was the first municipality in the prefecture.
If you pay Furusato tax and choose an electronic ticket as a return item, 30% of the donation amount will be sent to the designated smartphone.
When purchasing a product, it shows the screen of the product ticket, and the shop side contacts the stamp-type dedicated equipment and settles it.
They cannot be sold or sold.
Recipients usually require a certain amount of time from application to arrival, but electronic goods tickets can be received instantly.
Tourists can use it easily.
In addition to the five Hometown Tax Portals, there are also two special sites in the city.
Currently, there are 13 member stores, aiming at 100 by the end of this fiscal year.
In June, the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications established a new system to regulate local products in order to prevent excessive competition between local governments, with the amount of return goods raised to less than 30% of the donation amount.
The city says, "It is planned that merchants who handle local products will be affiliated stores and within the guidelines."
In the 18th year of Setouchi City, the hometown tax amount is about 430 million yen.
