Driving in high heels is dangerous!
Accidents involving the wrong pedal of young people - Yahoo!
Violations against road traffic laws
The number of reports on accidents caused by incorrect operation such as pedal treading is increasing, and it is a big mistake to think that this is a problem only for elderly drivers.
According to the 2015 National Police Agency data, there were more than 1080 cases aged 24 or younger, exceeding 1032 cases aged 75 or older.
It is important to call attention to young people as well.
do you want to take your feet?
is it safe?
There is no description of the gender ratio or cause of this data, but unlike elderly people who are often thought to be due to a decline in their bodies, such as driving skills and reflexes, in the younger generation, it is possible to mistake inadvertently due to other things such as music, conversation, etc.
In particular, women choose various shoes depending on their day's clothing, such as high heels, pamps, sandals and mules, and they drive as they are.
Some people say it is troublesome to change clothes while knowing that it is not suitable for driving, but some people do not think about the possibility that it will lead to danger at all, and many people drive without evil.
However, driving in high heels and sandals violates road traffic law.
The first is to ensure that the steering wheel, brakes and other operations are operated. Article 70 of the Act stipulates that "the operation should not be carried out to cause accidents and harm to people."
The other is Article 71, which stipulates that drivers must comply with the matters stipulated by the Public Safety Commission of each prefecture.For example, in Article 12 of the Miyazaki Prefectural Road Traffic Law Enforcement Regulations, there is a statement that drivers must not drive vehicles (except light vehicles) by wearing shoes in a manner that prevents driving operations, or by wearing shoes that may interfere with driving operations.
In each prefecture, even if it is not specified as a high heel, it is the same purpose to consider driving as a violation of " footwear that may interfere with driving operation."
So why is driving at high heels dangerous?
It is obvious considering the basics of safely pedaling.
For safe pedal operation, first put the foot to be perpendicular to the brake pedal, and when stepping on the accelerator pedal, tilt the foot to the right as a starting point.
At this time, regardless of the behavior of the car, it is important to keep it firmly fixed so that it does not break.
However, in high heels, the area where the heel is grounded on the floor is small, and the heel always blurs out, and because the height of the heel has an angle throughout the foot, the area of the foot that is grounded on the pedal becomes smaller and it is difficult to make fine adjustments that can not be firmly trampled.
This may lead to danger.
In addition, most cars have floor carpets, but this material is easy to catch a high heel, and sometimes when the heel is pulled and the pedal is not trampled, or when the heel is pulled, the high heel is removed and stuck inside the pedal.
In addition, there is a case where the heel pulls to the back of the pedal when stepping back from the pedal, and the accelerator pedal disappears.
Toyota and Subaru Accelerate joint development (response) including new AWD vehicles and 86/BRZ next-generation models - Yahoo!
Toyota and Subaru agreed on a new business capital alliance on September 27.
Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares and become an affiliate of the equity method.
Since the agreement in 2005, the two companies have been working together to produce Toyota vehicles, supply Toyota vehicles to Subaru, and jointly develop the FR sports car 86.
In June this year, we agreed to develop EV-only platforms and EV vehicles using Subaru's All-wheel drive technology and Toyota's electrification technology.
In this agreement, Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares.
At present, Toyota's shareholding in Subaru is 16.83% of the voting rights.
The company is a subsidiary of Toyota Corporation.
On the other hand, Subaru will acquire Toyota shares equivalent to the same amount (up to 8 billion yen) as the amount required to acquire Subaru shares.
Both companies develop and strengthen cooperation through business capital alliances.
Joint development of the AWD and 86/BRZ models, expansion of the THS (Toyota Hybrid System) to Subaru vehicles, coordination in the connected area, technical cooperation in the autonomous driving field, etc.
U.S., at least 18,000 people in three consecutive years | Shizuoka Shimbun
The U.S. Department of State announced on October 26, that it will reduce the number of refugees accepted from all over the world to 18,000 in fiscal 2020.
The minimum number of refugees since 1980 has been renewed for three consecutive years.
The Trump administration aims to appeal to the conservatives the strict immigration and refugee policies in the presidential election next year.
People who are driven out of the country in various places are constantly being criticized by human rights organizations.
The previous Obama administration set a limit of 110,000 in fiscal 2017, but the Trump administration, which was inaugurated in January 2017, overturned it and reduced it to 50,000.
It has been reduced to 45,000 in FY18 and 30,000 in FY19.
