Korea-Bulgarian Summit on Cooperation in Nuclear Power Plants and Defense Industries (Bulgarian News) | Yahoo!
(SEOUL=Yonhap News) South Korean President Moon Jae-in met with Bulgaria's Prime Minister Borisov on his official visit to Korea on September 27 and discussed ways to expand bilateral cooperation.
This is the first time the Prime Minister of Bulgaria visited Korea.
President Moon welcomed the visit to Korea prior to the 30th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations next year, and appreciated Prime Minister Borisov's leadership leading the development of Bulgaria.
The two leaders appreciated the continued increase in trade and investment between the two countries amid the global expansion of protectionism and agreed to work together to expand economic cooperation in the future.
President Moon welcomed Bulgaria's policy of granting Korean companies the status of "strategic investors" and said that he hoped that Korean companies would promote investment in Bulgaria based on this policy.
In addition, he stressed that Korea can become the best partner for Bulgaria in the process of introducing nuclear power plants and modernizing defense, and called for attention and cooperation so that Korean companies can participate in the order of the Bulgarian government's nuclear power plants and the promotion of the defense industry.
In addition, they agreed to strengthen future-oriented cooperation in the battery and auto parts sectors of electric vehicles and renewable energy sectors.
Prime Minister Borisov hoped that close cooperation will be carried out in the ICT (Information and Communication Technology) and science, technology, and education sectors led by Korea.
He also talked about the peace process on the Korean Peninsula, and expressed his gratitude for the support of the Korean government's efforts towards peace consolidation on the Korean Peninsula, including the announcement by the President of the Republic of Bulgaria in support of the North-South and US-North Summits.
Prime Minister Borisov appreciated President Moon's will to build a peace regime on the Korean Peninsula and the efforts of the Korean government, and reiterated the firm support of the Bulgarian government.
The meeting was attended by Mr. Sung Yunmo, Secretary of the Ministry of Trade, Industry and Energy, Mr. Lee Hao-sho, Chief Economic Secretary of the Chong (President's Office) and Mr. Kim Hyun-jong, Second Director of the State Security Office.
During his visit to the United States, Mr. Kang Gyeong-fa, deputy director of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, also attended the first official of the department, Mr. Zhao Seong.
Local industry in Hyogo and Awaji Island, Kinki Ceramics Co., Ltd., which manufactures "Awaji tiles," filed for quasi-self-insolvency debt of approximately 2 billion yen (Imperial Data Bank) - Yahoo!
It was also affected by the sluggish housing market and the progress of "consumer roofing away" due to the frequent earthquake damage.
Kinki Ceramics Co., Ltd. (TDB Corporation Code:53173983, capital of 9.92 million yen, 881-8 Otani, Awaji City, Hyogo Prefecture, representative Yukizo Fukuhara, 44 employees) filed for quasi-self-insolvency at the Kobe District Court on August 30.
One applicant was Daichi Yoshida (1-10-8 Nishi-Tenman, Kita Ward, Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture), and another was Daichi Yoshida.
The company was founded in June 1895 and reorganized in April 1961.
At first, he started his business as a manufacturer of ibushi tiles, a local industry in Awaji Island, in Nishitan-cho, Mihara County (present Minamiawaji City) under the trade name of Kinki Kiln Co., Ltd.
In October 1986, Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd. merged into Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd. and succeeded the business of Kinki Sangyo Co., Ltd., but at the same time, the head office was moved to its present location after changing its present name.
After that, sales offices were established in Fukuyama City, Hiroshima City, Oita City, Miyazaki City, etc., and Ibushi tiles were mainly used in the past, but due to changes in consumer demand, Western-style tiles such as flat plate tiles were manufactured at 70% and Ibushi tiles were manufactured at 30%.
The company has established a wide range of sales bases mainly in western Japan, including major house manufacturers, construction materials trading companies, and roof construction companies.
He was well known as the top tile maker of Awaji Island.
However, demand continued to grow due to the sluggish housing market following the Lehman shock and the frequent damage from the Great East Japan Earthquake and the Kumamoto Earthquake.
In terms of profits, in addition to a decline in the profit margin due to the surge in fuel prices, the company suffered a continuous deficit with excessive interest-bearing debt associated with inventory burdens and business fixed investment, and was forced to make severe financing.
For this reason, the Bank sought to rebuild its business by requesting financial institutions to ease the conditions for repayment of borrowings, but there was no sign of a recovery in business conditions, and financial conditions gradually began to tighten.
I couldn't help but abandoned the business continuity and this was the measure.
The debt is currently under investigation, but it is estimated to be about 2 billion yen.
Prefectural Dinosaur Museum in Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture, which promotes the industrialization of tourism (photographed with Japanese aerial photographs and small drones)
Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture, announced on September 25 that it will acquire approximately 25,000 square meters of land adjacent to the construction site of the road station "Dinosaur Valley Katsuyama," which will open next spring.
In order to accelerate the "industrialization of tourism" advocated by the city and local economy, we aim to attract accommodation-specific hotels and restaurants.
On the same day, the Board of Directors explained to the City Council's Special Committee on Invitational Base Development.
In addition to the opening of the Hokuriku Shinkansen in the spring of 2023, the entire section of the Chubu Centrair Expressway will be opened, and the prefectural Dinosaur Museum (Katsuyama City) will be renovated and enhanced.
It is a private resting place next to the east of the road station construction site.
Surrounded by the Kuzuryu River, Takinami River, and prefectural roads, it is twice as large as a roadside station (about 12,000 square meters).
Under the name of the industrial complex, the City Land Development Corporation will proceed with land negotiations from this fiscal year, acquire land, and build land in FY21.
According to the city, private businesses such as farmers' restaurants and harvest experience facilities, fast food, and restaurants have already begun to expand their businesses.
