BITPoint, which leaked 3 billion yen worth of crypto assets, resumed service (Genfusha Gold Online) - Yahoo!
In July of this year, crypto asset exchanges, which amounted to 3 billion yen such as bitcoin, were leaked illegally.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., the operator, announced on September 30 that it would resume the service of sending crypto assets (remittance).
There seems to be a certain point of view, including measures to prevent recurrence.
BITPoint that leaked Bitcoin and Ripple this July
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., which operates the Crypto Asset Exchange BITPoint, announced on September 27 that it will resume its Crypto Assets Transfer Service at around 14:00 on September 30.
In addition to responding to customers and communicating with the Financial Services Agency, there seems to have been certain points, including measures to prevent recurrence, such as management management system including security.
Bitpoint Japan says, "We will resume our services as soon as possible, while putting safety first, and will strive to recover the trust of users."
In July of this year, a cryptocurrency asset fraud incident worth 3 billion yen, including Bitcoin and Ripple, occurred at the exchange.
In the subsequent press conference, regarding the continuation of the business, he mentioned that "There is a current account balance of about 3 billion yen even if the compensation is deducted" "We aim to resume the service as soon as possible based on the priority of user protection."
This article was released on September 27, 2019.
