1 year from the Eastern Iburi Earthquake: Water supply even when power outages proceed with the installation of "watering plugs" directly connected to the water pipes Hakodate Mansion: Hokkaido Shimbun
In response to the total power outage (blackout) caused by the Iburi Eastern Earthquake in September last year, measures are being taken at condominiums in Hakodate City, where water breaks out.
According to the Water and Sewer Department of the City Bureau of Enterprises, seven condominiums were installed in one year after the earthquake.
There are about 400 condominiums and private housing units in the city that supply water with a "passenger tank type" that can be cut off during power outage, and the department calls for consideration of countermeasures.
The house's water supply system is broadly divided into two types: the "passenger tank type" for water once placed in the receiving tank located underground or on the roof, and the "directly connected type" for watering directly from the city's water distribution pipe to each door.
Even if the water pipe is not damaged, electric pumps that pump water from the water tank to each door will not be able to run due to power failure, and each door will be cut off.
Training (Aomori Broadcasting) - Yahoo!
Training was held in Shingo Village to search and rescue people who had suffered before the autumn mushroom harvest season.
60 people participated in the training held at Hirakozawa Forest Park in Shingo Village from the police, fire and hunting party.
At the opening ceremony, Mr. Tsukeda, Chief of the Goto Police Department, called for close cooperation and training.
★ Takahashi Regional Manager's declaration "We will start mountain training rescue training from this."
The training was based on the assumption that a man who went out to see the mushroom harvest would not return home even at night.
The participants are divided into three groups and search through the mountains with the names of missing men.
In Shingo Village, a 70-year-old man who entered the mountain in June was missing and was rescued the next day.
During the training, I found a man who had been injured and checked the cooperation between search and rescue on a stretcher to go down the mountain.
