The reason YouTuber became a full-time employee.
Listen to the president who hired (bizSPA!
9/27 (Fri) 8:47
YouTuber is now very popular with young people.
Although it is not uncommon for companies to use it for advertising their own products, some companies have started a rare system called "YouTuber adoption" that they employ as regular employees.
Direct Marketing Mix Inc. (DmMiX) is the main business of CRM (customer relationship management).
What does it mean to adopt YouTuber?
We interviewed Mr. Yuki Kobayashi, Representative Director of DmMiX and Representative Director of Staff First, a subsidiary that was actually adopted by YouTuber.
i want to support young people who do their best with YouTuber.
What is YouTuber adoption in the first place?
Yuki Kobayashi (hereinafter referred to as Kobayashi): YouTuber is now a longing for many young people.
It is also ranked in the vocational rankings that elementary school students want to get in the future, and the number of young people aiming for will increase steadily in the future.
Until now, we have adopted and supported young people chasing dreams such as bandmen and comedians.
In the same way, "YouTuberr Adoption" is to adopt and support young people who are chasing their dream of becoming YouTuber.
YouTuber has an image that individuals voluntarily post videos, but why did you decide to adopt YouTuber?
Kobayashi: While many young people are longing for the profession of YouTuber, there is a reality that most YouTuber is not able to make a profit as expected.
There are many creators who make and post videos while working part-time, and those who do not allow their family to recognize the existence of YouTuber.
In this initiative, we will provide an environment for creating salary and content for creators who have adopted it.
We will support our activities by supporting the disadvantage of the profession of YouTuber, which at first becomes unstable.
