New charges for mobile phones Price reduction with fair competition: Hokkaido Shimbun
A new fee plan for a mobile phone company was released as a result of the revised Telecommunications Business Act in October.
However, it almost stopped.
Chief Cabinet Secretary Yoshihide Suga said last summer, "There is room to lower the price by about 40%," and although expectations for price reduction were high, price competition did not occur.
It is a major factor that Rakuten's full-scale entry was postponed, and the oligarchy of three major companies continued.
It is desirable for consumers to have a fee system that is easy to use by fair competition.
I want to ask for the efforts of mobile companies.
The revised Act prohibits set discounts for terminal and communication charges.
Instead of selling the terminal fee, the communication fee was set to increase.
SoftBank and KDDI (au) announced plans to make the device a maximum of half the price.
However, both companies have a SIM lock that cannot be used by other companies for 100 days.
NTT DOCOMO makes up to one-third of the terminal cost for subscribers of its own lines.
The three companies continue to "enclosure" to prevent transfers to other companies.
The Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications announced that it would require immediate termination of SIM locks.
The company needs to respond quickly.
Rakuten's postponement was due to the lack of communication networks such as base stations.
It was expected to be a detonator of price reduction competition, so it looked like a shoulder strap.
It may have been the sweetness of the outlook.
The timing and prices of full-scale services have not been disclosed.
As a company responsible for social infrastructure, we would like to take responsibility for our business.
The price revision was triggered by the remarks of Chief Cabinet Secretary Suga.
Mr. Suga expressed dissatisfaction with the new fees of the three companies, saying, "I think competition will start from now on, and I do not think that it will be okay."
However, the government-made price reduction does not seem to distort the market and promote sound competition.
The company should develop customer-oriented competition before it is announced by the government.
The cost system of each company is very complex and it is not easy to compare.
The Consumer Affairs Agency called attention to the fact that there are cases where the consumer's burden exceeds half the amount while the terminal advertises such as "maximum half."
Companies must make careful and easy-to-understand explanations to avoid misunderstandings by themselves.
Cache Card for 3 Shinkin in Mie Prefecture - Ise Shimbun
Three Shinkin Banks in Mie Prefecture (Kuwana Mie Shinkin Bank, Kita-Ise Ueno Shinkin Bank, and Kihoku Shinkin Bank) announced on February 26 that they decided to reduce their withdrawal limit by cash card to prevent damage from special scams.
For depositors aged 70 or older who have not made a certain amount of withdrawal transactions at ATMs for the past three years, the maximum amount that can be withdrawn by cash card is 500,000 yen.
On October 1, the Kuwana Mie Shinkin Bank and the Kita-Ise Ueno Shinkin Bank were lowered from November 1.
In the prefecture, there are many special fraud cases in which cash cards and PINs are stolen by financial institutions, police officials, etc. and sent out at ATMs.
