Publication of the original manuscript before the suicide of Akutagawa | Shizuoka Shimbun
A manuscript written by Ryunosuke Akutagawa, first published in the Tabata Bunshimura Memorial Hall
The author Ryunosuke AKUTAGAWA (1892-1927) obtained the manuscript of his essay "Shoku Bungei, too literary," which he published in his last years, fighting literary theory with Junichiro TANIZAKI, by 27th at the Tabata Bunshimura Memorial Hall in Kita Ward, Tokyo.
It will be exhibited at the museum from October 1.
Although it was known that his essay was included in the whole collection, it was the first time that his manuscript was published publicly.
It is thought that he wrote it a few months before Akutagawa committed suicide, and the museum researcher, Takeshi Tanei, said, "I can see how Akutagawa, who was both mentally and mentally debilitated, faced serious literary challenges with a tragic resolution."
Twelve essays containing 200 characters were published in the April 27 issue of Bungei Shunju.
