Jaguar F-PACE, the first major improvement ...The possibility of hybridization (response) - Yahoo!
Jaguar's first crossover SUV, "F-PACE" The camera captured the new improved prototype for the first time in Southern Europe.
The F-PACE was the first four-seat concept SUV to be released in 2013.
The five-seat version was released in 2014 and officially debuted at the Frankfurt Motor Show in 2015.
The first model was released in 2016 and this is the first facelift.
The prototype captured is covered with thick camouflage, but part of the new design can be seen.
The headlights are more compact and thin, and the side air intake seems to be fixed to a sporty oval.
The grill is completely disguised, but there is no doubt that it will be redesigned.
In the rear end, some of the revamped taillights with elongated reverse lights on the top can be seen.
There is a possibility that the design that moves greatly to the side like the current model is compactly modified.
In the cabin, the company's touch screen infotainment system is expected to be installed, and new digital clusters, HVAC control screens, steering wheels, and gear selectors will be refreshed.
The powertrain is expected to include a 2.0-liter four-cylinder turbodiesel and a hybrid 3.0-liter six-cylinder indium.
The world premiere will be in 2020.
