Okayama Art Exchange opens in the center of the city: Sanyo Newspaper Digital | San Diego
People around the classroom who will be the setting for a video work depicting the future 3,000 years later
The international art exhibition "Okayama Art Exchange 2019" held every three years in central Okayama City (hosted by the executive committee of the city, prefecture, etc.) opened on the 27th.
Along with the mysterious title "IF THE SNAKE If Snake," 18 artists from 9 countries enjoy cutting-edge art created by art fans both in Japan and abroad.
This is the second time since 16 years, with French artist Pierre Yuig as artistic director, he has developed works that utilize Okayama's climate and local resources.
Approximately 40 films and three-dimensional works will be shown at 13 locations including the former Uchiyama Shimoko (Marunouchi, Kita Ward, Okayama City) and the prefectural Tenjinyama Cultural Plaza (Otenjin-cho).
Prior to the opening, a small opening ceremony was held, and about 100 people attended.
Mr. Masao Omori, Mayor of the Executive Committee, and Mr. Yasuharu Ishikawa, General Producer of the Executive Committee, said, "The works that stimulate intellectual sensibilities and stimulate imagination and creativity are scattered, and it becomes an exhibition that attracts attention from the world."
Families and children who visited the school immediately went to see a snake-shaped robot that responds to the sound of the surrounding area in the dohyo of the school yard, and walked around the school building that changed to the stage of a video work depicting the world 3,000 years later.
I enjoyed the art that came to a different world.
In his first year of high school in Tokyo (15), while traveling with his father, he said, "It's interesting to see a work that takes advantage of the atmosphere of the old school building and imagines the time it flows into this place."
It is closed on November 24 (the following day if it is a national holiday).
Hong Kong rally in 5 years of rain umbrella movement tens of thousands, aiming for general election | Shizuoka Shimbun
Five years have passed since the "Ambrella Movement" started, and people gathered at the meeting hall = 28th Hong Kong (co-operation)
[Collaboration with Hong Kong] On the 28th of May, a large-scale demonstration "Ambrella Movement" in 2014 called for democratization of the Hong Kong administration election, tens of thousands of meetings were held in a park near the Hong Kong government headquarters building in Admiralty, which had the largest base of the demonstration party.
Some young people occupied the main road around the venue and threw a fire bottle into the government building.
As protests started with the amendment of the Fugitive Ordinance continued, the participants renewed their determination to fight until the realization of a "true ordinary election" that could not be won at the time.
The protest, which began in earnest in June, was 112 days more than 79 days after the Umbrella Movement, and the demands of the demonstrators expanded to "five major demands" such as electoral reform.
